at0001.1.description: The unstructured name for the individual.
at0001.1.comment: The content of this data element may be derived from one or more components from CLUSTER.structured_name combined together as a text string. For example: 'John Markham', 'Professor Sir John Markham', 'John Markham Jnr MP'.

at0004.1.description: The relationship or role of the individual to the subject of the health record.
at0004.1.comment: For example - the copyholder of an advance care record; contact person in an organisation; relative in a family history entry; specimen collector; or witness to a fall or accident. If the individual being described using this archetype is the subject of the health record, then this data element is redundant.

at0001.1.comment: The DV_CODED_TEXT value set supports recording of the most common electronic communications used in health. at0002.1.description: The unique combination of alphanumeric characters, relevant for representation of 'Type'.
at0002.1.comment: For example: area code + landline phone/pager number; country code + mobile phone number; or email address.
